## Issue #1 - Single SDRAM CRT Output

Status: Open

Description:
Some users report builds supporting Single SDRAM function correctly through HDMI but fail to display video through CRT-based configurations.

Symptoms:
- Black screen
- No sync
- HDMI remains functional

Affected Configurations:
- Single SDRAM
- Direct Video
- Analog Output

Workaround:
- Use HDMI output
- Use previous Dual SDRAM release if CRT support is required

Investigation Notes:
Community testing suggests the issue may be related to FPGA compile configuration differences introduced during the transition from Dual SDRAM to Single SDRAM support.

Reference:
- GitHub Issue #1

